    "title": "In the AI era, \"product management\" should now mostly be context curation (and good goal-setting if you're operating closer to the 0‚Äì1 executive level).",
    "date": "2025-05-24",
    "content": "<p>In the AI era, \"product management\" should now mostly be context curation (and good goal-setting if you're operating closer to the 0‚Äì1 executive level).</p>\n<p>Literally collecting and indexing salient data, most of which is unstructured, all thoughtfully linked in @linear tickets.</p>\n<p>To collect the data, you need to set up standard telemetry (eg @getsentry, @posthog, @hotjar), conduct excellent discovery interviews (these will never be fully automated btw, only enhanced with AI in complementary ways, eg via @Vapi_AI pre-interview intake assistants and @howie_ai to accelerate progress by coordinating scheduling between team members) recorded via eg @firefliesai, and develop an uncanny sense of what matters in the particular part of a market (the \"terroir\" if you want to think of growing products with AI as a sort of cybernetic agricultural exercise) in which you're operating.</p>\n<p>Agents like <a href=\"https://claude.ai\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Claude</a> Code, when the development setup is right, can simply hook into those tickets, get a bit of guidance from models that are better at planning (@RepoPrompt -> Gemini 2.5 Pro via the @googleaistudio is my go-to), and then rip through development tasks, drawing from primary source context as needed via remote auth'd MCP servers maintained by the providers who steward the data and logic where that context resides.</p>\n<p>Engineers review PRs from @DevinAI, Codex, @codegen, Sentry auto-fixes, and <a href=\"https://claude.ai\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Claude</a> Code via GitHub actions, while saving the meatiest new features for 4-hour deep work cycles, working in a sort of pair programming setup with <a href=\"https://claude.ai\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Claude</a> Code (perhaps with a generator and a critic agent in different @Ghosttyorg tabs, where the critic has more sophisticated end-to-end tests with entire user journey level acceptance criteria, simulating a persona with goals via @browser_use or a computer use model with a clean context window but clear direction and context derived from the data captured during discovery and compressed into a composite profile).</p>\n",
