    "title": "Everyone's building AI strategies backwards.",
    "date": "2025-05-22",
    "content": "<p>Everyone's building AI strategies backwards.</p>\n<p>They see AI and immediately think: \"How can I do the same things cheaper?</p>\n<p>But after working with dozens of companies on AI transformation, I've identified three distinct roles that AI plays in organizations:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Growth Acceleration - AI supercharges marketing, sales, and customer acquisition</li>\n<li>Product Development - AI speeds up innovation cycles and feature delivery</li>\n<li>Discovery - AI reveals entirely NEW ways to serve your customers</li>\n</ol>\n<p>That third one? That's where the real magic happens.</p>\n<p>Here's why: When you only focus on optimization, you're playing within your existing boundaries. You're making your current box more efficient.</p>\n<p>But AI doesn't just optimize your box. It explodes the walls.</p>\n<p>Consider these examples:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>A recently promoted manager using team meeting transcripts to identify right person on his or her team to backfill their prior role (not just track performance)</li>\n<li>A Chief Revenue Officer discovering customer needs they never knew existed through conversation analysis</li>\n</ul>\n<p>A product team finding entirely new market segments by analyzing support tickets from a rabid, surprising user niche (e.g., paying close attention to these kinds of details is what allowed the founders of Justin dot tv to turn their company into Twitch, which was subsequently acquired by Amazon for over a billion dollars).</p>\n<p>The companies winning with AI aren't asking \"How can we cut costs?</p>\n<p>They're asking \"What couldn't we do before that we can do now?</p>\n<p>This requires a fundamental shift in thinking. It's about maniacally prioritizing the good of your customers‚Äîand then using AI as a \"macroscope\" to analyze the digital exhaust you generate at every touchpoint and discover surprising new ways to create value for them.</p>\n<p>Your competitors are racing to cut 20% of their costs.</p>\n<p>You could be discovering 200% more ways to serve your market.</p>\n<p>Which game do you want to play?</p>\n<p>What new capabilities has AI unlocked in your business that you couldn't have imagined two years ago?</p>\n<p>h/t Ben for a good chat this am in re this and more...</p>\n",
    "excerpt": "Everyone's building AI strategies backwards. They see AI and immediately think: \"How can I do the same things cheaper? But after working with dozens of...",
    "type": "post",
    "originalUrl": "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn%3Ali%3Ashare%3A7331396294235582466"
