    "title": "Emerging GSD at Work LLC summer AI lookbook (growth edition!):",
    "date": "2025-05-07",
    "content": "<p>Emerging GSD at Work LLC summer AI lookbook (growth edition!):</p>\n<p>What does it take to identify, land, and expand into a brand new market segment?</p>\n<p>I've been running some experiments the past few weeks (h/t to Viktoriya for hitting the gas), and, per some early signs of life, here are some of the tools worth considering adding to your AI stack:</p>\n<p>Core tooling:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://whisperflow.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Wispr Flow</a> / <a href=\"https://superwhisper.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">superwhisper</a> for dictation (stop typing!)</li>\n<li>Figma for collaborative whiteboarding</li>\n<li>Fireflies.ai for recording meetings</li>\n<li>Loom for async / remote coordination</li>\n<li>Upwork to help you fill in the gaps, where the growth team / software don't have capacity (make sure to scope RFPs and then assess responses with salient context from, e.g., Fireflies, and <a href=\"https://chat.openai.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">ChatGPT</a> o3!)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>GTM:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Google Gemini 2.5 Pro (especially via the Google AI Studio) for mining your treasure trove of unstructured data and getting clear on your target persona, strategy, and guiding policy before jumping into tactics (including, but not limited to massive meeting transcript + email inbox exports; putting these in a timestamped sequence is critical)</li>\n<li>OpenAI's <a href=\"https://chat.openai.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">ChatGPT</a> Deep Research for additional persona / market research, with to an eye toward what's beyond your proprietary digital exhaust repo (and content creation, but that's a post for another day...)</li>\n<li>Lovable for new landing pages (or entire websites tailored to the persona at a particular subdomain)</li>\n<li>Gamma for content creation (esp. packaging of insights derived from your existing data asset) & polish</li>\n<li>PhantomBuster for prospecting via adjacent digital watering holes (LinkedIn events, influencers' comments sections, etc.)</li>\n<li>Happenstance for identifying first-and-second-degree connections (beats standard keyword search by a mile); bonus points if you pool your contacts with your colleagues, board members, investors, et al</li>\n<li>Clay for enriching lead lists, esp. pulling salient info to qualify, prioritize, and help draft campaign messaging</li>\n<li>Shortwave  |  We're Hiring! for highly personalized emails directly from your outbox/primary domain</li>\n<li>Dripify.co for light LinkedIn automation</li>\n<li>Reply for email (and LinkedIn) outbound</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://vapi.ai\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Vapi</a> for call touchpoints (inbound & outbound)</li>\n<li>Swan AI for visitor identification -> ~AI SDR engagement (I'll be trialing others in the weeks ahead as well, and will share what I learn: seems like there's a whole lot of good, bad, and ugly in this particular space)</li>\n<li>Taplio for prioritizing content to engage with (DON'T PUT THIS ON FULL AUTO! Quality > quantity always...), published by the influencers your prospects trust</li>\n</ul>\n",
