    "id": "post-2025-03-09-7304521562085339137",
    "title": "Probably the highest ROI thing you can do right now from a retooling / learning pe...",
    "date": "2025-03-09",
    "content": "<p>Probably the highest ROI thing you can do right now from a retooling / learning perspective is to build a simple web application that solves a little problem for a colleague with:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://claude.ai\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Claude</a> Code (simple terminal app - link in comments),</li>\n<li>a \"smart\" IDE like Windsurf, and</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://chat.openai.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">ChatGPT</a> via the MacOS native app to ask clarifying questions while building (turbo-charge the whole thing by using your voice to drive the system with <a href=\"https://whisperflow.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Wispr Flow</a> for short-form instructions and <a href=\"https://superwhisper.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">superwhisper</a> for longer-form \"thinking aloud\"); critical that you sufficiently understand how the system works ‚Äî or at least the constituent parts</li>\n</ul>\n<p>(GitHub, deployment via Vercel/Heroku, DB hosting, etc., you can figure out if you just use the aforementioned tools to learn along the way.)</p>\n<p>Accept nothing less than enthusiastic validation of value delivered from said colleague, set a hard limit of no more than 8 hours to work on this project (and commit to deleting the entire thing and starting over if you don't cross the finish line by then), and you will gain more practical knowledge that is strongly correlated with income potential than a course, hours of YouTube, etc.</p>\n<p>What used to take financing, time, and a specialized team can now be accomplished by motivated generalists (with input/feedback from SMEs, given the problem you're tackling) in just hours ‚Äî and the first step toward realizing this personally is to commit to making something WITHOUT the recently obviated limiting belief that you can't because you aren't a software engineer by education or professional background.</p>\n",
