    "id": "post-2025-01-12-7284346351704784896",
    "title": "GSD AAA",
    "date": "2025-01-12",
    "content": "<p>In practice, meaningful AI adoption (what it looks like when \"things go right\" via the GSD AAA Playbook) is some combination of:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>higher-fidelity data acquisition via new, discursive media (e.g., bespoke voice assistants via <a href=\"https://vapi.ai\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Vapi</a> in lieu of surveys, passive capture of live human interactions via Fireflies.ai or Granola, as well as \"digital exhaust\" emitted during asynchronous collaboration through Loom videos) that complements existing records, e.g., PDFs, CRM logs, corporate knowledge base articles;</li>\n<li>turn-key entry of intent via <a href=\"https://superwhisper.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">superwhisper</a> or <a href=\"https://whisperflow.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Wispr Flow</a> (i.e., get your thoughts directly into the computer via dictation, which is 3x faster than typing) + salient contextual data into state-of-the-art models (mastery of key commands and window snapping tools like Magnet or Rectangle are critical for preserving user attention ‚Äî highly recommend getting an ultra-wide monitor as well);</li>\n<li>rigorous analysis via \"thought partnerships\" with e.g., Anthropic's <a href=\"https://claude.ai\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Claude</a> Pro, <a href=\"https://o1.ai\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">o1 Pro</a> via OpenAI's <a href=\"https://chat.openai.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">ChatGPT</a>, that accelerate the process by which the human user (the \"pilot\") teases out actionable insight from the raw material (the goal is, generally, to figure out what's new that's true ‚Äî and then what you should DO), supported increasingly by</li>\n<li>delegation of \"deep research\" tasks to proto-agentic systems* and specialized search products like Perplexity, Google Gemini 1.5 Deep Research, Happenstance (for mining your network), and even Upwork for publishing micro-RFPs (pro tip: ask <a href=\"https://o1.ai\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">o1 Pro</a> to generate RFP outlines with milestone-based compensation at the $100, $1000, and $10k levels to see what you might get at each level of budget); towards the end of</li>\n<li>publication of a \"charismatically compressed\" work product that is hyper-tailored to grab and hold the attention of your audience (often a colleague), via the \"best fit\" medium, e.g., interactive podcasts via Google's NotebookLM, a Gamma slide deck, an interactive <a href=\"https://claude.ai\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Claude</a> artifact (published via a Pro link or even a full web app per Replit's one-click deploy functionality), or just a razor-sharp email/Teams/Slack message with a long-form Loom video with a CTA button that links to a voice assistant in the postscript.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>In short, this tech allows for serious reengineering of existing workflows √† la BPR in \"single-player mode,\" from which whole new forms of \"multiplayer\" team collaboration can emerge; the key is figuring out what that looks like for you, your team, and your business through rapid experimentation (with healthy constraints, e.g., aim to get something done in two hours vs. two days), regular knowledge sharing.</p>\n",
    "excerpt": "In practice, meaningful AI adoption (what it looks like when \"things go right\" via the GSD AAA Playbook) is some combination of: higher-fidelity data...",
    "type": "post",
