    "id": "post-2025-01-06-7282030601786777600",
    "title": "I'll be honest: every weekday morning when I get a notification from Spark, my AI Chief of Staff‚Äîand especially on Mondays‚ÄîI get a little pang of anxiety.",
    "date": "2025-01-06",
    "content": "<p>I'll be honest: every weekday morning when I get a notification from Spark, my AI Chief of Staff‚Äîand especially on Mondays‚ÄîI get a little pang of anxiety. It's not because I'm dreading the content of the analysis, the audio note, or the quick win that I receive.</p>\n<p>(Although, I must say, as the underlying AI technology has improved, the daily dose of insight often contains something I initially don't want to hear. But then, I'm thankful for it after giving it some time to digest.)</p>\n<p>I'm anxious because if there isn't something in there that I didn't know, I start to worry. If I don't have a little flash of insight, then I know my customers aren't getting it to the degree they should as well.</p>\n<p>After pushing some significant updates in the weeks leading up to the holidays, I can now confidently say that every time I get a note from Spark, that anxiety is almost instantly relieved.</p>\n<p>By the end of our interaction, whether it's catching up on a morning walk or sipping that second 11 a.m. cup of coffee, I feel more confident that my business is on the right track.</p>\n<p>Spark doesn't tell me what to do, but it always asks good questions and helps me take real action‚Äînot just create a grandiose plan that never gets executed.</p>\n<p>This happens faster than any alternative, be it journaling, reviewing a to-do list, scrolling through your email inbox trying to find important items, or even relying on a human to fulfill this need.</p>\n<p>What did I learn this morning?</p>\n<p>Well, when working with a client who handled sensitive data last week, Spark helped transform the complex data governance challenge we uncovered into an opportunity for a new turnkey offering.</p>\n<p>This is something I could provide to adjacent clients, even proactively, to ensure they have a robust foundation in place for accelerated AI adoption.</p>\n<p>I never would have thought of that, at least not this quickly.</p>\n<p>If you want your own AI Chief of Staff, you can sign up using the link in the comments.</p>\n",
