    "id": "post-2025-01-05-7281685326987726848",
    "title": "(Cont'd from pt. 1, linked in comments.)",
    "date": "2025-01-05",
    "content": "<p>(Cont'd from pt. 1, linked in comments.)</p>\n<p>Now, getting the material out of your head and onto the \"page\" can be a challenge, especially initially, so I recommend two steps, in ascending order of cost:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Record all of your meetings with eg @firefliesai, and on a weekly basis, set a recurring 2-hour block (Friday mornings are good), where you select the best 3‚Äì5 meetings from the week, pop the transcripts into <a href=\"https://o1.ai\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">o1 Pro</a> or <a href=\"https://claude.ai\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Claude</a>, and ask it to hit you with \"three extremely precise, hard-hitting follow-up questions‚Äîas if you were an expert journalist‚Äîthat refer to the primary source material where appropriate, and if sufficiently addressed would be most likely to elicit some genuinely fruitful insight\" (or something like that). Go for a long walk, throw in the AirPods, turn on the voice memo app, and peek at each question, answering them via monologue until you're satisfied with where you land. Iterate by pasting what you say into the chat.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Usually takes twenty or so minutes of spoken thought to get somewhere interesting in my experience. Take the transcript and work with AI to turn it into a little post or two you can publish or schedule.</p>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li>Hire a human thought partner to meet with you at some cadence and record a \"private podcast\" you can mine for additional content. This person should be aware of your overarching goals, be fun to speak with, and will cost more than <a href=\"https://claude.ai\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Claude</a> of course but I would recommend.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>There's a third emerging growth mechanism I'm going to try soon via @spark_powerline on X ‚Äî imbuing your core product value prop into a clearly AI-based persona (possibly with access to custom tooling and your proprietary data asset) that provides the tiniest bit of help with a succinct question or one-liner in response to an explicit or implicit need latent in a post. I expect that this could actually work pretty well, and the compute spend would be justified since it allows you to put hundreds of low hours ands to work at the top of the funnel, a spend amount that would have been basically useless with ads or even a human social manager. We'll see...</p>\n<p>Really excited about this space in general ‚Äî big opportunity for people with durable expertise who really care about quality and their craft to expand their operation and gain leverage through software, and without external financing!</p>\n<p>H/t Mark Amtower and Stewart Alsop for being great thought partners √† la 2)</p>\n",
    "excerpt": "(Cont'd from pt. 1, linked in comments.) Now, getting the material out of your head and onto the \"page\" can be a challenge, especially initially, so I...",
    "type": "post",
