    "title": "Ok, so my* \"first 24h\" review of Cognition Devin thus far is it is very real, very powerful, and really a glimpse of where all this AI stuff is going ‚Äî and I think would be a no-brainer purchase for someone who was already a skilled engineering manager.",
    "date": "2024-12-18",
    "content": "<p>Ok, so my* \"first 24h\" review of Cognition Devin thus far is it is very real, very powerful, and really a glimpse of where all this AI stuff is going ‚Äî and I think would be a no-brainer purchase for someone who was already a skilled engineering manager.</p>\n<p>I've already delegated:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>a bug fix based on the content of a Sentry alert +</li>\n<li>some vague direction about styling an html template (which I delegated to the Replit Agent as well, and tbh Devin seemed to have done a better job ... it seemed to have been able to intuit some pretty subtle stuff in re how elements were styled elsewhere and then automatically brought that into the suggested code changes without being explicitly prompted to do so)...</li>\n</ol>\n<p>...and it seems to have one-shotted both (even though I didn't set it up with everything it needs to adequately test, etc. b/c I've never actually onboarded a dev before or actually collaborated on a git repo, so it's a bit of a learning curve).</p>\n<p>Now, my main problem atm is that it is doing things that are way beyond my own experience / expertise (I'm literally having to learn what a PR is, how to think about the process of reviewing someone's code, getting Devin set up with .env creds, creating separate environments, package management, etc. ... all this stuff I sort of knew of but never had to actually muddle my way through before ‚Äî my process has been mostly brute force copying and pasting relevant content) ... but, that's kind of what you have to do if you're going to starting hiring specialists anyway.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>I am not a SWE; I am a word-person (and have been a pretty vocal 'agent' skeptic, though I'm having to revise my perspective in light of o1, etc.) with an MBA who took one CS class in undergrad who is also very impatient and technically-literate-enough that I've been able to direct Chat, <a href=\"https://claude.ai\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Claude</a>, et al and iterate fast enough that I've been able to grow my services business over the past 2y and launch 2x software products (really one meaningful one) that generate monthly recurring revenue w/o having hired a single FTE.</li>\n</ul>\n",
