    "id": "post-2024-11-26-7267296248976523264",
    "title": "What if your search engine could stop you from making a bad decision before you even knew you were about to make it?",
    "date": "2024-11-26",
    "content": "<p>What if your search engine could stop you from making a bad decision before you even knew you were about to make it?</p>\n<p>We've become so accustomed to typing queries into search boxes that we've forgotten a crucial truth: the most valuable insights often come from being asked the right question at the right time.</p>\n<p>I believe the next evolution in AI isn't about better answers‚Äîit's about better questions. And it's closer than you think.</p>\n<p>In this article, I explore:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Why our expectations in re reactive internet search is holding back business decision-making</li>\n<li>How proactive AI questioning will transform how leaders work</li>\n<li>What this future actually looks like in practice</li>\n</ul>\n<p>After spending the last two years building in this space, I'm convinced this shift will fundamentally change how executives access and use information.</p>\n<p>Curious to hear your thoughts: What questions do you wish your technology would ask you?</p>\n<p>h/t Mark Amtower for helping me get this into shape!</p>\n",
