    "id": "post-2024-11-20-7265094347807723520",
    "title": "for the stuff you can't delegate to AI, use Upwork:",
    "date": "2024-11-20",
    "content": "<p>for the stuff you can't delegate to AI, use Upwork:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>record a Loom video (ramble for as long as you'd like), explaining in general what you need, acceptance criteria, etc. (I just did this for a video editing job w/ specifics around redaction)</li>\n<li>pipe the transcript through o1-preview (accessible via paid Chat accounts or the OAI dev portal) and ask it to create a bespoke Upwork RFP, including pricing & packaging</li>\n<li>post</li>\n<li>copy and paste every proposal back into the o1-preview chat and ask it to pick the best person for the job</li>\n<li>back to work</li>\n</ol>\n<p>AI is super helpful both for compression (this has been the case for a while) and reasoning (crafting the terms of the contract, then selecting the best candidate!, via o1).</p>\n<p>I've done this a bunch of times now and have only had good experiences, w/ almost zero management overhead.</p>\n",
