    "id": "post-2024-11-11-7261868143503986688",
    "title": "The new o1 model from OpenAI is useful for:",
    "date": "2024-11-11",
    "content": "<p>The new o1 model from OpenAI is useful for:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>analysis (esp. teasing out contrarian insights),</li>\n<li>bespoke pricing and packaging,</li>\n<li>complex negotiation, and...</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Valuation??</p>\n<p>Here's your prompt du jour ‚Äî copy and paste your entire codebase into o1, either via Chat or the OpenAI developer playground and ask it to come up with a fair-market price...</p>\n<p>Then, ask, \"what would have to be true for it to be 10x that?</p>\n<p>And finally, tell it to give you one single action you can take right now in 60 seconds or less to move things in that direction.</p>\n<p>[8 weeks ago, I wrote my first line of code for the new product I'm working on. >4KLOC and 5 customers later, o1 seems to think things are at least somewhat on track :) ]</p>\n",
