    "id": "post-2024-09-02-7236346049429217280",
    "title": "Great set of notes and I strongly agree with the general premise.",
    "date": "2024-09-02",
    "content": "<p>Great set of notes and I strongly agree with the general premise. We are in many ways like Wylie Coyote, already having run off the cliff, even if the tech doesn't improve much from here. The impact will certainly be felt over the next decade or two.</p>\n<p>One general piece of advice that I would add to the different items that you note in your document is this: young people should not only consider switching their major or the area of focus in their studies, but also figure out how they can get a customer or client to pay them ‚Äî however small the amount ‚Äî to solve some very real problem right now.</p>\n<p>And with these general purpose tools like <a href=\"https://claude.ai\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Claude</a>, AI note takers, etc., the faster you can figure out what the nature of the problems are and the type of work that allows you to maintain high energy levels, the better. Leverage AI to get high quality reps in 10 times as quickly and then increase the marginal value ‚Äî and thus pricing ‚Äî of the types of services you're able to provide.</p>\n<p>What you learn from this process is absolute gold and information that I believe is necessary, but perhaps not sufficient, to figure out how you need to reorient your trajectory. There is literally no reason to wait to do this.</p>\n<p>Now, you could certainly ignore this advice and go down some conventional career path in a large and probably bloated corporation where widespread use of these tools is not yet the norm and focus on learning how to execute against internal processes that will soon be obsolesced; and you might make a fine salary in the process if you're able to get the gig in an increasingly competitive job market (although it'll be at that point relatively even more difficult to retool vs. people who rode the wave).</p>\n<p>Or, you can proactively figure out what you should be doing at the intersection of these true 21st century technologies and start going down the right path TODAY.</p>\n",
    "excerpt": "Great set of notes and I strongly agree with the general premise. We are in many ways like Wylie Coyote, already having run off the cliff, even if the tech...",
    "type": "post",
    "originalUrl": "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn%3Ali%3Ashare%3A7236346049429217280"
