    "title": "AI products probably worth building:",
    "date": "2024-08-22",
    "content": "<p>AI products probably worth building:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>pipeline that reliably redacts sensitive information from raw multimedia eg Loom videos, Fireflies A/V (publish more compelling long-form content, more often; everyone gets a \"reality show\" that can be mediated by AI for the good stuff w/o someone having to actually consume the whole thing, but no third-party's secrets are shared)</li>\n<li>enterprise reporting on all the data submitted to the organization's LLM web app that somehow also preserves individual privacy (c-suite understands what people are using it for + what's actually happening in the org's \"unconscious mind,\" latent in the data, while also mitigating the chilling effect of users worrying about the legibility of their particular conversations)</li>\n<li>a sort of e2e integrated communication tool that allows you to record a Loom video, send it to someone, have it frontloaded with an extremely compressed and high-quality representation of the content (I do this manually by piping the content into 3 Opus before sending an email with the video link in the PS), and then allowing the user to jump into a conversation with a voice agent who continues the thread on your behalf and is pre-loaded with all relevant context in its system prompt, the transcript of which is shared with the sender in both compressed and raw form; I do this now manually by stringing together Loom, VAPI, and <a href=\"https://claude.ai\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Claude</a> (true async, remote, discursive, personalized communication)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>All of these things are sort of possible now but prohibitively expensive (measured in no. of clicks) to do as frequently as I'd like.</p>\n<p>Comment or DM if any of these resonate w you...</p>\n",
