    "content": "<p>If you want to take advantage of AI, but aren't serious about facilitating a fundamental transformation of the way work gets done in your organization to one that is:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>remote-native;</li>\n<li>asynchronous-by-default;</li>\n<li>connected to a global, fractional talent pool;</li>\n<li>driven by uncertain outcomes anchored in a deep unifying desire to move toward them; and</li>\n<li>composed of lean, liquid, high-trust teams of a-players who prefer \"hiring AI\" ad hoc vs. empire building;</li>\n</ul>\n<p>...then your efforts will ultimately be for naught.</p>\n",
