    "content": "<p>This-gen AI is most useful as a COMPRESSOR, not a GENERATOR.</p>\n<p>You need to first acquire high-quality, salient, rich, proprietary data to make it useful‚Äîand then work with the systems to figure out how to make good decisions (eg by using <a href=\"https://claude.ai\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Claude</a> to augment your own hypothesis generation) that, in turn, help you acquire more...</p>\n<p>Good use rewards originality, risk-taking, and novelty; if what you end up with is more of the same (the buzzy term for this is \"slop\"), then you're doing it wrong.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Help people solve difficult problems.</li>\n<li>Record the process.</li>\n<li>Use those recordings as input to AI make sense of what you learn, share insights, and accelerate progress with snappier follow-up communication and action, teaching others how to do what you've figured out, and/or building bits and pieces of software.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>More is more. Now, go get the good stuff!</p>\n",
