    "title": "Just wrapped another 2-hour \"private podcast\" with Stewart Alsop!",
    "date": "2024-07-26",
    "content": "<p>Just wrapped another 2-hour \"private podcast\" with Stewart Alsop!</p>\n<p>Covered a lot of ground ‚Äî now I'm wondering which of the following topics to write about...</p>\n<p>‚ö°Ô∏èAI as Electricity: Draw an analogy between AI and the introduction of electricity, discussing how AI could fundamentally change how organizations operate and enable new modes of production, similar to how electricity transformed factories. Explore the implications for corporations and knowledge workers.</p>\n<p>üìùThe Importance of Systems of Record: Discuss the critical role that systems of record (e.g., CRMs, financial data) play in organizations, especially as they grow. Highlight how these \"sacred centers\" enable trust, alignment, and decision-making.</p>\n<p>üëÅÔ∏èBalancing Privacy and Transparency in the Age of AI: Explore the challenges organizations face in maintaining privacy while leveraging AI technologies that rely on vast amounts of data. Discuss the potential consequences of the \"chilling effect\" on experimentation and innovation if privacy is not adequately protected.</p>\n<p>üìàEmpowering Outside Sales with AI: Share insights on how AI could transform the way outside sales teams operate by making it easier for them to enter and retrieve information from systems of record. Discuss the potential benefits for CEOs and executives in having more timely access to frontline data.</p>\n<p>üßë‚ÄçüíªThe Rise of the Remote-Native Organization: Reflect on how AI is enabling new forms of asynchronous and remote work, and how this could lead to the emergence of \"remote-native\" organizations. Explore the implications for team structures, communication, and productivity.</p>\n<p>„Ä∞Ô∏èNavigating the Hype Cycle of Enterprise AI: Provide guidance for executives on how to cut through the hype around enterprise AI and focus on finding high-impact use cases. Discuss the importance of empowering \"AI whisperers\" within organizations to drive adoption and value creation.</p>\n<p>üß†The Evolving Role of the Scribe in the Age of AI: Draw parallels between the historical role of the scribe and the emerging role of AI in organizations. Discuss how AI can augment and enhance knowledge capture, decision-making, and institutional memory.</p>\n<p>Curious about any of these?</p>\n<p>Say so in the comments, and I'll post more!</p>\n<p>PS ‚Äî thanks to <a href=\"https://claude.ai\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Claude</a> 3 Opus for distilling these only minutes after we wrapped the convo :)</p>\n",
