    "id": "post-2024-06-15-7207885374692454402",
    "title": "Every month I do a private podcast with Stewart Alsop.",
    "date": "2024-06-15",
    "content": "<p>Every month I do a private podcast with Stewart Alsop.</p>\n<p>He's a great interviewer and helps me make sense of all of the data I'm generating and trends that I'm noticing in my work, plugging AI into organizations, small and large.</p>\n<p>On Friday we covered a lot of ground, including:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>how leaders under pressure can make good decisions when it comes to bringing the technology in-house;</li>\n<li>why digital transformation isn't binary and organizations that reach their desired state may end up looking, may take on a hybrid structure;</li>\n<li>how capabilities like rapid intelligence collection and analysis, which were only historically available to states and major corporations, are increasingly available to smaller organizations;</li>\n<li>why it's absolutely critical that decision makers get hands-on with the tools;</li>\n<li>hyper-individuation, unprecedentedly diverse career paths, and what that might mean for the future of knowledge work;</li>\n<li>and finally, perhaps most interestingly, the things that WON'T change and how if things go right, AI may actually help us become more human.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>I'll try to turn some of these into posts over the next few weeks.</p>\n<p>Which topics are you most interested in?</p>\n<p>Let me know in the comments.</p>\n",
