    "title": "I'm going to start recording the Loom videos of me doing some processes (complicated prospecting/research to start).",
    "date": "2024-05-15",
    "content": "<p>I'm going to start recording the Loom videos of me doing some processes (complicated prospecting/research to start). I'll be doing as many reps as I can for about an hour.</p>\n<p>Then, I'll be posting an RFP with the video and an AI-generated explanation on Upwork, to see who can simply do the same thing and work through the other 90% of the queue.</p>\n<p>To delegate effectively in a world with AI and global liquid labor markets, it would seem to me that there are a lot of these batch processing tasks, where one can go from zero to one, and then one to ten and then delegate the rest. This is without having to hire someone or turn it into a full blown operational workflow.</p>\n<p>This liminal space wasn't really available to traditional corporations before, but now, it's probably feasible and viable for parties on the buy and sell side. This is all thanks to the technology that enables more information and labor liquidity, and brings down the barriers of space, culture, time, and context.</p>\n<p>I am excited to experiment more with this.</p>\n<p>Anyone else getting good value from Upwork?</p>\n",
