    "id": "post-2024-05-11-7195048290629885952",
    "title": "The future of SDR outbound feels something like your voice agent (with access to your private/company data) calls the prospect's voice agent and talks for as long as you want.",
    "date": "2024-05-11",
    "content": "<p>The future of SDR outbound feels something like your voice agent (with access to your private/company data) calls the prospect's voice agent and talks for as long as you want.</p>\n<p>You, as the caller, pay for both parties' compute ‚Äî and you can scale this up horizontally to run a ton of simulations.</p>\n<p>If there are unresolved gaps or surprising opportunities, they should be latent in the transcript, which can be, again, summarized and mined by AI systems that are aligned with the interest of one party or the other.</p>\n<p>The recipient should be able to make the choice of whether or not to escalate to asynchronous or even live interaction.</p>\n<p>Bigger the prize, the more compute you should be willing to pay for.</p>\n<p>Sales and marketing spend has already started shifting from labor to capital with performance marketing. It would seem to me that the voice agent thing would accelerate that trend.</p>\n",
