    "date": "2024-05-09",
    "content": "<p>Once you realize that the utopians and dystopians are similarly wrong about how the AI thing is going to play out, it really frees you up to think clearly about the future in such a way that you can take action right now.</p>\n<p>The success of your business in this new paradigm isn't pre-determined. Your size, industry, etc. matter a lot less than you think.</p>\n<p>What does matter is that you're willing to think about what lies beyond the commonly accepted horizon line of your industry and commit to arming your organization's internal pioneers with powerful tools that they can use to figure out what works and what doesn't (you'll be surprised in both cases).</p>\n<p>That has very little to do with technology and a lot to do with mindset.</p>\n<p>It all starts with a willingness to focus on the frontier, accept that you don't (you can't) know what's out there, and then commit to finding out what is.</p>\n",
