    "date": "2024-05-09",
    "content": "<p>The pandemic introduced us to a liquid, remote & asynchronous mode of work.</p>\n<p>I believe we‚Äôre never going back.</p>\n<p>Here‚Äôs why ‚Üì</p>\n<p>Ambitious CEOs need their teams to be agile.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Risk-taking</li>\n<li>Adaptable to market changes</li>\n<li>Willing to think innovative & outside the box</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Rigid organizational structures encourage team members to conform.</p>\n<p>Now, they‚Äôll likely follow the status quo.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>They‚Äôll stick to the same schedules</li>\n<li>They‚Äôll follow the same processes</li>\n<li>They‚Äôll never question anything</li>\n</ul>\n<p>And that‚Äôs dangerous.</p>\n<p>Remote, flexible work environments do the opposite.</p>\n<p>Team members have significantly more degrees of freedom.</p>\n<p>And with this freedom, comes the accountability & ownership of their work.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>They‚Äôll be forced to get disciplined</li>\n<li>They‚Äôll figure out ways to enjoy work</li>\n<li>They‚Äôll constantly be incentivized to make things better</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Imagine if every team member starts showing these qualities.</p>\n<p>You‚Äôll slowly build an A team, that stands out from the competition.</p>\n<p>Have you tried going fully asynchronous at your company yet?</p>\n<p>I‚Äôm curious to know about your experiences.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>**</li>\n</ul>\n<p>PS ‚Äì With AI & OKRs, you can run a high-performance team with only 1 live meeting!</p>\n<p>Would you like me to give a walkthrough?</p>\n<p>Let me know in the comments.</p>\n",
