    "id": "post-2024-05-07-7193633228237271041",
    "title": "Steps for enterprise AI success:",
    "date": "2024-05-07",
    "content": "<p>Steps for enterprise AI success:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Arm employees with SOTA tools that align with corporate policy (e.g., <a href=\"https://chat.openai.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">ChatGPT</a> Enterprise, <a href=\"https://claude.ai\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Claude</a> 3 Opus via AWS Bedrock in a web app with SSO login).</li>\n<li>Pay close attention to product analytics. Actions reveal preferences, and it's easier to drive adoption with people who are already motivated to use the general purpose tools.</li>\n<li>Identify 1-5 power users (their usage will follow a power law curve) and help them become 10x engineers/lawyers/SDRs/[insert knowledge worker role] by investing in additional capabilities and one-on-one empowerment working sessions with an expert outsider.</li>\n<li>Streamline their workflows with minimal + rapid custom software development where appropriate to make it easy for their peers (who will become organically interested when they see the 10x results) to pick up the new tooling. Catalyze user-led innovation with self-serve tooling that simplifies experimentation and pay attention to what works. Drive this with 30-day hyper-focus on moving one KPI.</li>\n<li>When you're ready to go big, convene a cross-functional cyborg superteam to tackle an uncertain frontier outcome that would meaningfully change the trajectory of your company over the course of a quarter.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Cultivate data assets in the process, learn, and keep the cycle going to go further, faster than ever before!</p>\n",
