    "title": "Thought-provoking perspective from Cheryl Cui, Co-Founder & CEO of Bota Bioscience...",
    "date": "2024-05-06",
    "content": "<p>Thought-provoking perspective from Cheryl Cui, Co-Founder & CEO of Bota Biosciences, on how AI can accelerate frontier innovation:</p>\n<p>What we see, AI, because of the knowledge structure is so different from human education, it become a generalist in many disciplines. You would enable some of the specialized researchers, I use biologist as example, have a cohort of chemists and programmers working for it to enable its ideas. I think that's the beauty of AI, that would open up something other than just the labor efficiency aspect of things, but bring novelties and innovations to the world.</p>\n<p>Beyond productivity gains, word-crunching AI can serve as a translation layer, enabling highly specialized experts from different fields to communicate and collaborate more efficiently.</p>\n<p>Executives across industries should consider not only how these tools might make their teams more efficient at what they're already down, but also how AI might supercharge diverse, cross-functional teams of deep experts to drive outsized progress on the frontier.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://lnkd.in/gehEdjTf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://lnkd.in/gehEdjTf</a>\",<a href=\"https://youtu.be/vO9SKlGdzzw?feature=shared\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://youtu.be/vO9SKlGdzzw?feature=shared</a>,\",MEMBER_NETWORK</p>\n",
