    "id": "post-2024-05-05-7193022839707303936",
    "title": "AI has bent the iron triangle of project management.",
    "date": "2024-05-05",
    "content": "<p>AI has bent the iron triangle of project management.</p>\n<p>Given the same cost constraints and quality criteria, you may be able to attain your desired state 2‚Äì10x faster.</p>\n<p>Leaders can/should tackle bigger, more complex problems + expect compressed learning cycles.</p>\n<p>Quick wins with LLM-powered tools that fit into your teams' existing workflows are good for building trust and momentum; but, if you want transformative results (and don't want AI-native upstarts to eat your lunch in 5-7 years), you'll need something stronger.</p>\n<p>Successful AI initiatives can't be sustained by a CAIO's top-down mandate alone.</p>\n<p>Durable change starts with bottoms-up user-led innovation: Give everyone access to powerful, general purpose tools and see who really pushes the limits.</p>\n<p>Then, when you're ready, assemble a tiger team of internal AI pioneers to tackle a gnarly problem on the frontier of your industry ‚Äî reduce time-to-value for your best customers by 10x with new product features shipped in hours, not weeks; turn SDRs into cyborgs who close prospects on the first call; spin up swarms of AI analysts that mine actionable insights from PAI, and use them to get inside your competition's OODA loop.</p>\n<p>When it comes to succeeding with this new generation of AI, speed is critical.</p>\n<p>If you're serious about integrating the tech into your business, don't wait ‚Äî raise your expectations, focus on the frontier, and accelerate.</p>\n<p>Ready to go big and go fast with generative AI? Send me a DM to get started.</p>\n",
