    "title": "Valuable skills are transferable.",
    "date": "2024-05-02",
    "content": "<p>Valuable skills are transferable.</p>\n<p>October 2022: I faced one of the toughest transitions of my life.</p>\n<p>Shutting down my startup ‚Üí Becoming an Indie consultant</p>\n<p>My co-founder and I had poured 2 years of our lives into the startup.</p>\n<p>Time, money, and an unbelievable amount of energy.</p>\n<p>To shut it down was soul-crushing.</p>\n<p>For 36 hours, I had a pity-party.</p>\n<p>I questioned everything, felt horrible, and even pessimistic at times.</p>\n<p>But then, a wave of realizations hit me:</p>\n<p>It had positives to look at.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>I had developed valuable skills in the process (OKRs)</li>\n<li>I had demonstrated value-creation in a complex market</li>\n<li>I had built strong connections in the industry</li>\n</ul>\n<p>And this got me back up!</p>\n<p>I connected with one of my business connections and got my first deal as an OKR consultant.</p>\n<p>Since then, over 14 months, I‚Äôve worked with 20+ clients through my solo independent boutique consultancy GSD @ Work.</p>\n<p>And consistently,</p>\n<p>I‚Äôve noticed how the skills I learned have transferred into this next phase.</p>\n<p>Not only am I happy about the bets I‚Äôve made,</p>\n<p>But I‚Äôm also enjoying the flexibility that comes with this mode of business.</p>\n<p>In the end,</p>\n<p>One lesson stands out for me!</p>\n<p>Something I‚Äôd repeatedly want to tell myself.</p>\n<p>Attempting to solve a difficult problem you are intrinsically motivated to solve never goes to waste.</p>\n<p>We had set out to transform the entire mental health profession.</p>\n<p>The challenge was big. But we were mission-driven, high-energy & determined to make a difference.</p>\n<p>On the journey, battling all the problems that came our way, we developed processes and systems that are valuable to the market.</p>\n<p>Those same systems help me solve different problems elsewhere through my indie agency GSD @ work.</p>\n<p>Looking back, I‚Äôm proud of the value we created.</p>\n<p>And the decisions we took.</p>\n<p>Whole-hearted attempts at value creation always reward you.</p>\n<p>There's immense power in resilience.</p>\n<p>And sometimes, a closed door leads to paths we never imagined :)</p>\n",
    "excerpt": "Valuable skills are transferable. October 2022: I faced one of the toughest transitions of my life. Shutting down my startup ‚Üí Becoming an Indie consultant My...",
    "type": "post",
    "originalUrl": "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn%3Ali%3Ashare%3A7191798741891256320"
