    "title": "Even as an MBA graduate, I believe management is underrated as an art and an area of academic research.",
    "date": "2024-04-29",
    "content": "<p>Even as an MBA graduate, I believe management is underrated as an art and an area of academic research.</p>\n<p>It's a very salient topic given the downward pressure AI puts on transaction costs.</p>\n<p>(The Coasean firm must exist only so long as tx costs are high. What happens in the world where there's significantly more information and labor liquidity at a global scale? What does that mean for the \"nature of the firm\" in the 21 c.?)</p>\n<p>I'm doing some ressourcement to think about the implications at a deeper level: Drucker, von Hippel, Sloan...</p>\n<p>Who else should I read?</p>\n<p>Fayol maybe?</p>\n<p>Something from the field of cybernetics?</p>\n",
