    "title": "Most of what is written is not published.",
    "date": "2024-04-16",
    "content": "<p>Most of what is written is not published. Most of what is spoken is not written. Most of what is known is not verbally articulated.</p>\n<p>This would lead me to speculate that the most valuable data in the AI economy will be generated at the frontier through rapid experimentation, and it won't be documented in traditional ways.</p>\n<p>On one hand, you have the external world which can be captured with high fidelity sensors including, but not limited to, raw video and audio.</p>\n<p>Then you have the internal world of the actor. This is quite a bit more difficult to digitize, but traditionally, language has been the bridge between these two sources of tacit knowledge.</p>\n<p>I anticipate that future models will take advantage of hard-to-imagine instrumentation that goes beyond the usual media of text, images, and sound, making aspects of the internal and external worlds legible to computers.</p>\n<p>In other words: This is your daily reminder to cultivate a data asset!</p>\n<p>Here's how:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Stop typing and start talking: switch to dictation, e.g., with <a href=\"https://superwhisper.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">superwhisper</a></li>\n<li>Go async: use tools like Loom to record high-fidelity primary sources, then compress them into succinct messages and fire off both to your colleagues, collaborators, or clients</li>\n<li>Put your data assets to work: e.g., before your next high-stakes meeting, stuff all of the relevant context from your private repository (e.g., transcripts from Fireflies.ai, emails) into a conversation with Anthropic's <a href=\"https://claude.ai\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Claude</a> Pro (w/ Opus!), and ask it to help you rigorously prepare)</li>\n<li>Continue to find new ways to serve your customers (and help your \"neighbors,\" more generally), digitize the process and the results, keep everything super secure, e.g., MFA + passkeys on everything + add'l support from Agency Cybersecurity and continue to accelerate out on the frontier!</li>\n<li>üîÅ</li>\n</ol>\n<p>(Inspired by some of the insights in a recent episode of Nathan Labenz's excellent Cognitive Revolution podcast: <a href=\"https://lnkd.in/gcVBwT_W\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://lnkd.in/gcVBwT_W</a> )</p>\n",
    "excerpt": "Most of what is written is not published. Most of what is spoken is not written. Most of what is known is not verbally articulated. This would lead me to...",
    "type": "post",
