    "id": "post-2024-02-13-7163170036260540416",
    "title": "How do I identify use cases for ‚ÄúAI as an eager Assistant‚Äù?",
    "date": "2024-02-13",
    "content": "<p>How do I identify use cases for ‚ÄúAI as an eager Assistant‚Äù?</p>\n<p>Here‚Äôs the question I ask:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>What activities (that I perform daily) would I delegate if I found the right person?</li>\n</ul>\n<p>OR</p>\n<ul>\n<li>What activities (that I perform daily) do I consistently find at #2-3 on my to-do list?</li>\n</ul>\n<p>OR</p>\n<ul>\n<li>What activities (that I perform daily) do I find draining but I just HAVE to do for the business?</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you‚Äôre still going blank, here are 3 most common use cases I‚Äôve seen:</p>\n<p>ùü≠) ùó°ùóºùòÅùó≤-ùòÅùóÆùó∏ùó∂ùóªùó¥ & ùó†ùó≤ùó≤ùòÅùó∂ùóªùó¥ ùó¶ùòÇùó∫ùó∫ùóÆùóøùó∂ùó≤ùòÄ:</p>\n<p>Never take notes in meetings. Always ask AI to do that.</p>\n<p>This allows you to be hyper-attentive and make more valuable contributions in the meeting.</p>\n<p>Subscribe to Otter.ai or Read AI</p>\n<p>Your meetings will be tidy & organized forever.</p>\n<p>ùüÆ) ùóúùóªùó≥ùóºùóøùó∫ùóÆùòÅùó∂ùóºùóª ùó•ùó≤ùòÅùóøùó∂ùó≤ùòÉùóÆùóπ:</p>\n<p>Ask your assistant to search for the best books, concepts, and frameworks to solve a particular problem.</p>\n<p>Just specify the context, talk about the problem & ask AI to give you curated information.</p>\n<p>ùôéùôñùô¢ùô•ùô°ùôö ùòæùôùùôñùô©ùôÇùôãùôè ùô•ùôßùô§ùô¢ùô•ùô©: ‚ÄúHey! I have to run a weekly review meeting with my Marketing team. We are working on our first Linkedin campaign. Can you give me some questions to plan my meeting ? I want to understand the status & then be crystal clear on priorities‚Äù</p>\n<p>ùüØ) ùó†ùó∂ùóªùó∂ùóªùó¥ ùóúùóªùòÄùó∂ùó¥ùóµùòÅùòÄ & ùóîùó∞ùòÅùó∂ùóºùóªùòÄ:</p>\n<p>Ask your assistant to go through a dump of information and dig out pieces that you need.</p>\n<p>They might be contrarian insights, immediate actionable, unfair advantages, new strategies, etc.</p>\n<p>ùôéùôñùô¢ùô•ùô°ùôö ùòæùôùùôñùô©ùôÇùôãùôè ùô•ùôßùô§ùô¢ùô•ùô©: ‚ÄúHey! Here‚Äôs the transcript of a brainstorming call I had with my marketing team. I want you to go through this and give me all the different strategies we discussed in a table format. Add the potential benefits & roadblocks we discussed. Also give me a list of actions that we identified.‚Äù</p>\n<p>And if you want to take it to the next level,</p>\n<p>ùôéùôñùô¢ùô•ùô°ùôö ùòæùôùùôñùô©ùôÇùôãùôè ùô•ùôßùô§ùô¢ùô•ùô©: ‚ÄúHey! That‚Äôs great. Now act as my trusted advisor coach and highlight blind spots. How could the meeting have gone better? Come up with hard-hitting follow up questions for the team that would invite everyone to elevate quality of ideas in the next follow up session.‚Äù</p>\n<ul>\n<li>**</li>\n</ul>\n<p>These are the simplest ways you can start experimenting with AI.</p>\n<p>Remember,</p>\n<p>It only takes one good use case for you to feel the power of AI.</p>\n<p>Then you won‚Äôt be able to stop thinking of use cases.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>**</li>\n</ul>\n<p>PS ‚Äì If you‚Äôre looking for a full crash course to get up to speed with AI, I created this specifically for you:</p>\n<p>startusingai.carrd.co</p>\n<p>After this course, you‚Äôll know all secrets of the top 1% of AI users.</p>\n",
