    "title": "I have started using Midjourney as a visioning tool to enhance my goal-setting process.",
    "date": "2024-02-09",
    "content": "<p>I have started using Midjourney as a visioning tool to enhance my goal-setting process.</p>\n<p>Instead of the usual 4x4 OKR slide with text and charts, I've now grounded my weekly sync in an Apple Note, headlined with this image.</p>\n<p>It's mobile friendly, so I can walk a few miles and talk through what I've learned over the past week and consider paths forward.</p>\n<p>I record the whole thing via the Otter.ai iOS app and pop the transcript into Anthropic's <a href=\"https://claude.ai\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Claude</a> Pro at the end, asking it to help me generate additional ideas in re how to address the obstacles I've encountered in my monologue.</p>\n<p>The image contains lots of symbols related to my overall strategy, and returning to it helps me focus at the beginning of the session. I have found it especially compelling versus rote text.</p>\n<p>Building a business, especially when you're only accountable to yourself and your clients (in my case, 90% of whom I'm exclusively serve remotely), can be hard.</p>\n<p>These tools make it easier, and I'm grateful for them.</p>\n",
