    "title": "Navigating a technology business is hard.",
    "date": "2024-02-06",
    "content": "<p>Navigating a technology business is hard.</p>\n<p>The future isn‚Äôt just unknown. It‚Äôs unknowable!</p>\n<p>I use a mental model called ‚ÄúFoggy River‚Äù to simplify the goal-setting process:</p>\n<p>The journey of starting and growing a company is similar to crossing a \"Foggy River.</p>\n<p>There are 3 elements:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Where you are ‚Üí (your current position on the map)</li>\n<li>Where you want to be ‚Üí (your destination on the other side of the river)</li>\n<li>Why you exist, AKA your mission ‚Üí (‚ÄúNorth‚Äù on your compass)</li>\n</ol>\n<p>But here‚Äôs the problem:</p>\n<p>You can see the eventual destination, but you can‚Äôt see what‚Äôs in the middle.</p>\n<p>There‚Äôs fog everywhere.</p>\n<p>And there‚Äôs only 1 way to disperse the fog:</p>\n<p>By taking action, uncovering more information that lets you see further down the river.</p>\n<p>So the question of goal-setting is essentially this:</p>\n<p>From everything that you see (right now), which next stone will you step toward?</p>\n<p>There‚Äôs always a trade-off:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>You can prioritize depth</li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n<li>This means a faraway stone in a certain direction. Which means more progress! But what if our direction isn‚Äôt right?</li>\n</ul>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li>You can prioritize breadth</li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n<li>This means a closer stone that allows more degrees of freedom. Here we clear the fog before choosing a direction. But then we‚Äôre moving less fast :)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Navigating this choice is the art of goal setting.</p>\n<p>But in either scenario,</p>\n<p>Choosing 1 stepping stone & aligning our entire team‚Äôs efforts towards this one objective does wonders for a business.</p>\n<p>I covered this in detail in a workshop with one of my clients.</p>\n<p>If this analogy made sense, the workshop is a wonderful deep dive into how all the parts fit.</p>\n<p>Comment \"Foggy River\" if you're interested in the whole workshop recording.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>**</li>\n</ul>\n<p>And, let time me know your thoughts :)</p>\n",
