    "title": "How to Foster an AI-Ready Culture in Your Organization?",
    "date": "2024-01-19",
    "content": "<p>How to Foster an AI-Ready Culture in Your Organization?</p>\n<p>There are 2 pillars to the solution:</p>\n<p>ùü≠/ ùóñùóπùóÆùóøùó∂ùòÅùòÜ & ùóßùóøùóÆùóªùòÄùóΩùóÆùóøùó≤ùóªùó∞ùòÜ ùó∂ùóª ùó¶ùòÅùóøùóÆùòÅùó≤ùó¥ùó∂ùó∞ ùóúùó∫ùóΩùóπùó≤ùó∫ùó≤ùóªùòÅùóÆùòÅùó∂ùóºùóª</p>\n<p>AI initiatives fail when they‚Äôre NOT aligned with business goals.</p>\n<p>Here‚Äôs what you need to do:</p>\n<p>ùòãùò¶ùòßùò™ùòØùò¶ ùò§ùò≠ùò¶ùò¢ùò≥ ùò∞ùò£ùò´ùò¶ùò§ùòµùò™ùò∑ùò¶ùò¥</p>\n<ul>\n<li>What are the goals? What are the areas of improvement that we are focusing on? What would it look like if things *went right*?</li>\n</ul>\n<p>ùòäùò∞ùòÆùòÆùò∂ùòØùò™ùò§ùò¢ùòµùò¶ ùòµùò©ùò¶ ùò¥ùòµùò≥ùò¢ùòµùò¶ùò®ùò∫ (ùò¢ùòØùò• ùò±ùò≥ùò™ùò∞ùò≥ùò™ùòµùò™ùò¶ùò¥) ùòµùò∞ ùòµùò©ùò¶ ùòµùò¶ùò¢ùòÆ</p>\n<ul>\n<li>To ensure alignment and enhance opportunities for collaboration</li>\n</ul>\n<p>ùòöùò¶ùòµùò∂ùò± ùò∏ùò¶ùò¶ùò¨ùò≠ùò∫ ùò¥ùò∫ùòØùò§ ùò∂ùò± ùòÆùò¶ùò¶ùòµùò™ùòØùò®ùò¥</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Discuss progress & collectively brainstorm how AI can help you with specific use cases.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Encourage this behavior by posing ‚ÄúWhat would have to be true?‚Äù and ‚ÄúHow might we get there?‚Äù questions at the weekly sync meetings.</p>\n<p>Once your team understands the strategy fully and feels they‚Äôre a part of the journey, they‚Äôll start proactively searching for AI solutions that help them (and others) work faster & better.</p>\n<p>ùüÆ/ ùóñùòÇùóπùòÅùó∂ùòÉùóÆùòÅùó∂ùóªùó¥ ùóÆùóª ùó≤ùóªùòÉùó∂ùóøùóºùóªùó∫ùó≤ùóªùòÅ ùó∞ùóºùóªùó±ùòÇùó∞ùó∂ùòÉùó≤ ùòÅùóº ùó∞ùóµùóÆùóªùó¥ùó≤</p>\n<p>If your culture resists change, any *new* initiative will find it difficult to be embraced.</p>\n<p>Here‚Äôs what you need to do:</p>\n<p>ùòåùòØùò§ùò∞ùò∂ùò≥ùò¢ùò®ùò¶ ùòäùò∞ùòØùòµùò™ùòØùò∂ùò∞ùò∂ùò¥ ùòìùò¶ùò¢ùò≥ùòØùò™ùòØùò®</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Facilitate workshops, provide access to AI resources, and push team members to constantly educate themselves.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>ùòìùò¶ùò¢ùò• ùò£ùò∫ ùòåùòπùò¢ùòÆùò±ùò≠ùò¶</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Become curious about AI and bring it up during all discussions. Ask yourself, ‚ÄúHow can I use AI to get a desired result 10x faster?‚Äù</li>\n</ul>\n<p>ùòôùò¶ùò∏ùò¢ùò≥ùò• ùòåùòπùò±ùò¶ùò≥ùò™ùòÆùò¶ùòØùòµùò¢ùòµùò™ùò∞ùòØ</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Create a safe space for trial and error. Not every AI initiative will be a success, but each attempt is a learning opportunity. Give positive reinforcement for every failure where insights are shared with the broader team.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>ùòêùòØùò∑ùò¶ùò¥ùòµ ùò™ùòØ ùòõùò¢ùò≠ùò¶ùòØùòµ ùò¢ùòØùò• ùòõùò≥ùò¢ùò™ùòØùò™ùòØùò®</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Hire individuals with the requisite AI skills or upskill your current workforce. This could mean providing access to online courses or bringing in experts for in-house training sessions.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once your team starts enjoying the process of working with AI, it‚Äôs very hard to come back.</p>\n<p>Keep supporting their efforts, as I genuinely believe every business is only 1 ‚ÄúAha‚Äù moment away from becoming AI-powered forever!</p>\n<p>Start today :)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>**</li>\n</ul>\n<p>üìå Also, if you‚Äôre curious about AI but not sure where to start, I put together an email course to help you out.</p>\n<p>In 5 days, you‚Äôll learn how to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Free up 50-80% of your Time</li>\n<li>Build highly-engaged remote teams</li>\n<li>Beat the competition with superior products & services (without increasing your resources!)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Get it here for FREE: startusingai.carrd.co</p>\n",
