    "title": "My answer?",
    "date": "2024-01-17",
    "content": "<p>My answer?</p>\n<p>Aiming to deliver certain outputs over striving towards relatively uncertain outcomes.</p>\n<p>There‚Äôs always a temptation to set key results that can be achieved through the delivery of work products. Things like shipping a certain number of features, or producing documentation towards the end of making an internal process more efficient.</p>\n<p>However, the primary function of a solid OKR process is to reduce uncertainty on the frontier and generate insights that can be reincorporated into a company‚Äôs differentiated positioning in a marketplace and ultimately generate profit margins.</p>\n<p>Human beings hate uncertainty and there are two ways that you can deal with it. One is to try to reduce it by running experiments and staying humble on the frontier, especially with a high-performing cross-functional team. The other is to more or less stay put and avoid uncertainty as much as possible.</p>\n<p>It takes discipline and leadership to take the first path, and that‚Äôs where OKRs can be a helpful tool when wielded correctly.</p>\n",
