    "id": "post-2024-01-12-7151573592386805760",
    "title": "3 Tips to become an AI-powered business owner without heavily altering your existi...",
    "date": "2024-01-12",
    "content": "<p>3 Tips to become an AI-powered business owner without heavily altering your existing workflows:</p>\n<p>1Ô∏è‚É£ Stop typing and start talking.</p>\n<p>Switch to dictating communications instead of typing whenever possible.</p>\n<p>This allows you to communicate 3x faster, with higher quality output.</p>\n<p>Use Scribe, the <a href=\"https://chat.openai.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">ChatGPT</a> app with Whisper, or Super-Whisper to dictate emails, documents, and social media posts.</p>\n<p>The dictation-enabled increase in throughput and your newfound ability to iterate through more feedback cycles will lead to overall better results.</p>\n<p>2Ô∏è‚É£ Record everything to enable asynchronous communication.</p>\n<p>Use tools like Descript & Otter to record processes and meetings with automatically generated transcripts.</p>\n<p>You can then use AI to extract tailored information from the raw recordings.</p>\n<p>This reduces friction for remote team communication - And your team can work *much* more flexibly (and on their own terms).</p>\n<p>3Ô∏è‚É£ Integrate AI capabilities into existing tools over adding new ones.</p>\n<p>For example, build a Slack bot that connects to AI models through Zapier.</p>\n<p>Or use a simple web app interface to abstract away complex AI configurations.</p>\n<p>This makes adoption frictionless by meeting people's existing workflows.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>**</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The key is that all these little boosts compound.</p>\n<p>Each change is small. But over time, the impact on team efficiency and velocity is enormous.</p>\n<p>So, try them out.</p>\n<p>You‚Äôll be surprised to see how well it works!</p>\n",
