    "title": "While there's plenty of business and technical acumen that American entrepreneurs and industry technologists would be willing to contribute to the National AI Talent Surge, the experience of applying to federal roles isn't frictionless (yet).",
    "date": "2023-11-17",
    "content": "<p>While there's plenty of business and technical acumen that American entrepreneurs and industry technologists would be willing to contribute to the National AI Talent Surge, the experience of applying to federal roles isn't frictionless (yet).</p>\n<p>Even that first step of tailoring your current resume to meet federal guidelines can be a bit painful, so I figured, \"Well, why not use AI to make it easier?</p>\n<p>I took PDF versions of:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>resume guidelines from GSA.gov & USAJOBS.gov,</li>\n<li>a sample resume (ibid), and</li>\n<li>the Biden Whitehouse EO on AI,</li>\n</ul>\n<p>And created a \"federal resume coach\" to help prospective applicants get started.</p>\n<p>Note that this is very much a prototype (and custom GPTs are, in general, far from reliable), and you should always double-and-triple-check the information provided by an AI system; however, I'd recommend giving it a try by uploading the latest version of your resume and a PDF version of the role you're seeking (you can do this by hitting cmd+p on the job description page and then saving it as a PDF).</p>\n<p>The GPT will then take a crack at comparing the information in your resume vs. the guidelines in its knowledge base, provide a bit of coaching based on the gaps between what's in the JD and your background, and even ask follow-up questions (like a good coach would) to make the application process a bit easier.</p>\n<p>Again‚Äîthis is just a proof-of-concept, BUT I do believe that these are exactly the kinds of use cases where AI can help USG serve its citizens better (and vice versa) by reducing administrative overhead without actually changing the rules, making it easier for individuals to contribute their time and talents to roles in public service while still working within the existing system.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://lnkd.in/epzZ7PpH\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://lnkd.in/epzZ7PpH</a></p>\n",
    "excerpt": "While there's plenty of business and technical acumen that American entrepreneurs and industry technologists would be willing to contribute to the National AI...",
