    "id": "post-2023-11-06-7127380888975224832",
    "title": "Practical implications of today's announcements at OpenAI developer day:",
    "date": "2023-11-06",
    "content": "<p>Practical implications of today's announcements at OpenAI developer day:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Never stop acquiring high-quality, proprietary data*</li>\n<li>Upload that data into a custom GPT knowledge base</li>\n<li>Tailor custom instructions and API actions to help someone solve a repetitive, uninteresting task with that custom GPT</li>\n<li>???</li>\n<li>PROFIT!</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Even as capabilities grow, there will continue to be room for entrepreneurs to focus on the acquisition and \"shaping\" of high-quality data that's not in the foundation model.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Turns out data really is the new oil. We just needed a couple of tech breakthroughs to get us to the point that we're able set up digital refineries and distribution networks. There's value (raw material that can be turned into new knowledge) either under your feet today‚Äîor, out there in uncharted latent space, ready for you to start prospecting. Go forth and start wildcatting!</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Exciting news in re custom GPTs, new capabilities, lower costs, and forthcoming revenue sharing.</p>\n<p>Can't wait to start building.</p>\n",
