    "id": "post-2023-09-05-7104940257627774976",
    "title": "‚ÄúPeople are able to earn; people are able to learn.",
    "date": "2023-09-05",
    "content": "<p>‚ÄúPeople are able to earn; people are able to learn. You can do everything there [on Twitter].‚Äù</p>\n<p>I recently had a fascinating conversation with GEORGE WANDHE, a Kenyan software engineer and CS student whose story is an illustrative example of how IT (and AI in particular) is reshaping traditional career pathways.</p>\n<p>What sets George apart is his ability to harness the power of platforms like Replit to secure paid programming gigs, build a portfolio, and accelerate his education in new, specialized fields like AI and backend Python development ‚Äî and inspire his classmates to do the same.</p>\n<p>üõ†Ô∏è The Role of Replit and Bounty Systems</p>\n<p>Instead of traditional summer internships, George started by taking on small bounties on Replit. Over time, he demonstrated his credibility and reliability. Replit gave him the dual advantage of offering the tooling required to complete tasks and connecting him to economic opportunities through their bounty system. The platform became a meritocratic space where he could showcase his skills, independent of factors like educational background and location.</p>\n<p>üê¶ Twitter (now X) as a Multipurpose Tool</p>\n<p>George also leverages Twitter, not just as a space for networking and business opportunities but also as a source of practical knowledge. Through intentional curation, he gains access to a wealth of educational content from AI practitioners globally, propelling both his learning and earning capacities. It‚Äôs easy to dunk on Twitter (and social media more broadly) as a source of distraction and/or disinformation; George‚Äôs experience shows that, with the right perspective and intentions, it can unlock economic and educational opportunities.</p>\n<p>ü§ñ The Role of AI Tooling</p>\n<p>Integrated AI tools like Replit‚Äôs Ghostwriter and <a href=\"https://chat.openai.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">ChatGPT</a> Plus further supercharge learning for engineers like George. These tools serve as a ‚Äúpersonalized tutors,‚Äù helping practitioners make sense of complex knowledge bases, new APIs, and more ‚Äî ‚ÄùAI-as-thought-partner‚Äù ultimately allows individuals to connect mind and hand more robustly, across a wider range of problems.</p>\n<p>üåç The Implications</p>\n<p>George‚Äôs experiences represent what I perceive as a forthcoming seismic shift in how we should think about employment, education, and economic mobility:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>A trend toward more fluid, global labor markets.</li>\n<li>A shift from traditional education pathways to more specialized, real-world experiences.</li>\n<li>The role of AI as a personal thought partner and workforce multiplier.</li>\n<li>The changing dynamics of employment, moving from full-time roles to a more ‚Äúliquid workforce.‚Äù</li>\n</ol>\n<p>In the longer term, we might see ‚Äúliquid teams‚Äù come together to solve specific problems, compensated according to real-world results, rather than time invested (or outputs, for that matter).</p>\n<p>As we ponder the future of work, George's story offers us a compelling glimpse of what's possible at the intersection of AI and this new generation of digital natives, able to work from anywhere.</p>\n",
