    "title": "If you're the CEO of an SMB, the insights in these tweets (or \"posts\" now, I guess?",
    "date": "2023-08-24",
    "content": "<p>If you're the CEO of an SMB, the insights in these tweets (or \"posts\" now, I guess?) from Peter Wang & Sam Lessin are worth meditating on.</p>\n<p>Software is fundamentally a technology that turns labor into capital.</p>\n<p>When you write code, you are literally encoding your expertise and making it available to others, self-serve.</p>\n<p>And, thanks to AI (especially GPT-4 & tools like GitHub <a href=\"https://copilot.microsoft.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Copilot</a>), the fixed costs of software development are dropping like a rock (literally, you can build a fully customized, AI-integrated web application that makes one of your operators significantly more efficient in 2 hours or less.)</p>\n<p>This means that software development capabilities that were previously only available to enterprises, technology companies, and VC-backed startups are now available to SMBs, niche services firms, and even sole proprietors.</p>\n<p>Vertical integration will be the name of the game, and there's no better time to start on this path than RIGHT NOW.</p>\n<p>All you need is 2 hours with an expert (to provide input in re their problem-solving process) and OpenAI's GPT Plus Code Interpreter plugin...</p>\n",
