    "title": "For a successful AI implementation, you need 3 core ingredients:",
    "date": "2023-08-22",
    "content": "<p>For a successful AI implementation, you need 3 core ingredients:</p>\n<p>üî≠ An executive sponsor who wants to make forward progress on the frontier of their industry: They strive for excellence, and they‚Äôre willing to achieve their goals by trying something new.</p>\n<p>ü•á A motivated operator who cares deeply about quality and seeks to master their craft: They have the will and skill to become the ‚Äú10x engineer‚Äù equivalent for their role‚Äîa true force multiplier to whom their peers can look for inspiration.</p>\n<p>‚û∞ A translator (traditionally a ‚Äúproduct manager‚Äù) who can make things with AI, understand the higher-order business objectives, and (in real-time) weave together a bespoke solution that helps the operator become more efficient AND moves the needle on the chief executive‚Äôs strategic priority.</p>\n<p>During my recent chat with Dmitri Tcherevik  we discussed our experiences on the front lines of AI and how all successful implementations seemed to have this archetypal structure.</p>\n<p>Are you a pioneering executive with an early adopter / master operator on your team who wants to take their work to the next level?</p>\n<p>Share what you‚Äôve observed in a comment below‚Äîand send me a DM if you‚Äôre ready to cut through the hype and start plugging #AI into your business.</p>\n",
