    "id": "post-2023-06-27-7079282197043539968",
    "title": "Let's be honest ‚Äî typing is...awkward.",
    "date": "2023-06-27",
    "content": "<p>Let's be honest ‚Äî typing is...awkward.</p>\n<p>It's unnatural.</p>\n<p>And there's no reason why we should constrain our interactions with personal computers to mice and keyboards.</p>\n<p>When clients ask me how they should start using AI to become more productive, my first answer is always the same: \"Stop typing, and start talking.</p>\n<p>In fact, even the fastest typists are less than half as efficient at communicating (measure in words per minute) as the average person can speak.</p>\n<p>And speaking is just a little slower than the speed of thought.</p>\n<p>Thanks to breakthroughs like OpenAI's state-of-the-art Whisper transcription model (available for free in the <a href=\"https://chat.openai.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">ChatGPT</a> iOS app!), we can return to our roots and engage more naturally with our personal computers (and each other through digital media).</p>\n<p>Thought is the fundamental input to knowledge work, so the faster you can codify your thoughts via digitized natural speed‚Äîgiven that you're working on the right problem, using reasoning skills, investing unbroken attention into solving the problem at hand, and so forth‚Äîthe more value you can create, which is ultimately what leads to technology development, growth, and the creation of real wealth.</p>\n<p>Take the first step by downloading the <a href=\"https://chat.openai.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">ChatGPT</a> app on iOS, tapping on the audio icon to converse naturally with GPT-4, and start working with your AI thought partner to elevate the quality of your own ideas, make headway on tasks that keep getting bumped to no. 2 on your to-do list, and start using your computer in a way that keeps you in an uninterrupted state of flow.</p>\n<p>Soon, we'll wonder how we ever used our devices in any other way.</p>\n<p>#ai #technology #artificialintelligence #transcription</p>\n",
