    "id": "post-2023-04-18-7054143220657655809",
    "title": "If you want to take advantage of AI, then you should focus on QUALITY, not QUANTITY.",
    "date": "2023-04-18",
    "content": "<p>If you want to take advantage of AI, then you should focus on QUALITY, not QUANTITY.</p>\n<p>It's tempting to try to use it for the purposes of the latter; but, you can gain the most leverage by focusing on the former.</p>\n<p>What do I mean by this?</p>\n<p>Early attempts at using the tech have largely been focused on multimedia generation (text, images, etc.), which have unfortunately been used to scale up bot outreach & phishing operations and churn out blogspam.</p>\n<p>Now, AI (and LLMs in particular) can be fantastic tools that catalyze the create process...but \"AI\" isn't creative per se.</p>\n<p>It's useful to think of it primarily as a \"translation layer\" that can help you shape and compress raw material into something that precisely fits an unmet informational need via a particular medium (e.g., a LinkedIn post, an email, a meeting summary), given three critical inputs:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\"Raw material,</li>\n<li>Context about the present, and</li>\n<li>A desired outcome.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Raw material can be generated in three ways, in ascending order of least to most valuable:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Digital exhaust: information you can collect from disparate parts of the internet (I have been increasingly using AI to mine insights from podcast backlogs, where participants are more likely to reveal valuable information & tacit knowledge not written anywhere else)</li>\n<li>Your own mind: contemplative activity‚Äîincluding meditation & dialogue‚Äîcan help you make sense of the raw input you've been collecting over a certain period and make it into something new (I try to do this w/ daily walks & morning monologues, recorded on my phone, which I sometimes turn into content)</li>\n<li>Contact with reality: high-fidelity recordings of value creation with/for clients that results in the creation of economic surplus, happy customers, and cash flow from operations (e.g., Zoom recordings of client sessions)</li>\n</ol>\n<p>AI-as-translation-layer allows you to handle much a much larger QUANTITY of information inputs towards the creation of a much higher QUALITY essential output that adds value + a unique perspective to the public body of knowledge that is more likely to attract the right type of attention and ultimately act as an asset for your business.</p>\n<p>By collecting the raw material and turning it into a format that's legible to machines (e.g., via speech-to-text transcription), you can then prompt the machine to further compress it into insightful, tailored nuggets that you can publish and share for your customers and prospects.</p>\n<p>As my writing professor taught me in grad school, \"writing is actually mostly thinking, not typing,\" so by delegating the typing to AI, you free up cognitive resources to collect and refine more interesting raw material.</p>\n<p>Interested in learning how to use GPT-4 & Whisper to turn your raw experience into valuable marketing assets and \"write better with AI\"?</p>\n<p>Let me know in the comments.</p>\n<p>Enough interest, and I'll create a video tutorial.</p>\n<p>#ai #artificialintelligence</p>\n",
