    "id": "post-2023-04-03-7048670892087791617",
    "title": "Are you interested in learning how to use AI, but aren't sure where to start?",
    "date": "2023-04-03",
    "content": "<p>Are you interested in learning how to use AI, but aren't sure where to start?</p>\n<p>Here's how I've been using artificial intelligence‚Äîalmost daily since last fall!‚Äîto boost my efficiency, effectiveness, and provide more value to clients:</p>\n<p>üëÇ Better Listening in Meetings: By recording meetings and creating transcripts using Google Meet, I can focus more on what's being said and recall crucial details in follow-up communication. For example, before sending a check-in email to prospects, I revisit the transcript, find one or two items they were interested in but we didn't dig into, and then do a little research into the topic, including a valuable insight that recalls our discussion and provides some free value.</p>\n<p>‚úçÔ∏è Creating Higher-Quality Content, 10x FASTER: I use Vienna Hypertext's Scribe app to record monologues during my morning weekday walks and automatically transcribe them. Then, I shape the raw material with the help of OpenAI's GPT-4, Grammarly for copy edits, and Midjourney to create an eye-catching image for engaging text posts (including this one). More recently, I've been experimenting with D-ID and ElevenLabs for AI-generated audio and video.</p>\n<p>üö∂‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è Getting More Active: Incorporating AI into my workflow has allowed me to work on-the-go (literally dictating to my phone, rather than typing on a laptop), resulting +10,000 steps per day. I use iOS speech-to-text to \"write\" and \"read\" material with Speechify.</p>\n<p>üëÅÔ∏è Consuming Content Efficiently: I use summarize.tech for YouTube videos and Snipd for podcasts to save time and focus on the most relevant information. This has helped me mine insights from long-form content and be more discerning in where I put my attention.</p>\n<p>üë®‚Äçüíª Building Functional Software: <a href=\"https://chat.openai.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">ChatGPT</a> Plus helps me write and debug Python code for my projects, while Replit offers a marketplace for developers when I need extra help.</p>\n<p>üí¨ Providing Rapid and Precise Feedback/Instruction to Colleagues: I use Descript to record feedback and instructions (e.g. pitch deck first reads, where I verbalize my thoughts), then compress the transcript using <a href=\"https://chat.openai.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">ChatGPT</a> Plus into TL;DRs that I send with the video. This has improved communication and saved a TON of time (say, vs. traditional written summaries via email or Docs).</p>\n<p>üó∫Ô∏è Exploring New Frontiers of Knowledge: AI helps me dive deep into topics relevant to my clients, identify top researchers, and even simulate panel discussions to understand different perspectives.</p>\n<p>It's essential to note that AI is not perfect, and you should always double-check AI-generated outputs before sharing them with clients or team members.</p>\n<p>But, once you start using AI to free up attention and energy to invest into building relationships, uncovering insights, cultivating a unique perspective, and spending more time in reality (unchained from your desk!), you'll never want to go back.</p>\n<p>Of the use cases above, is there one you'd like me to create a tutorial for? LMK in the comments!</p>\n<p>#ai #artificialintelligence</p>\n",
