    "id": "post-2023-03-17-7042489420515540992",
    "title": "Digital media are fundamentally changing before our eyes (and ears).",
    "date": "2023-03-17",
    "content": "<p>Digital media are fundamentally changing before our eyes (and ears).</p>\n<p>Right now, thanks to AI (and soon, AR/VR), our relationship with digitized info is becoming more immersive, discursive, and personal.</p>\n<p>What does that mean practically?</p>\n<p>We've become accustomed to clicking and scrolling through web pages, but there's a new emergent paradigm at the intersection of these enabling technologies: in lieu of websites, we'll have conversations with intelligent agents that can rapidly product a charismatic synthesis of proprietary information relevant to our immediate needs.</p>\n<p>And as soon as our needs exceed what the agent can address, we'll get kicked up the value ladder until we reach the ultimate source, a chief executive or expert solopreneur coordinating the information and machinery necessary to produce new knowledge in his or her monopolized niche.</p>\n<p>Just as we didn't stop speaking/listening with the advent of the printing press or reading after radio and television were invented, we will continue to click and scroll through web pages; however, this new paradigm presents opportunities for entrepreneurs and innovators who have been looking for a tech-enabled source of leverage.</p>\n<p>Again, what does this mean practically?</p>\n<p>Well, if you've got an idea, you can get started NOW by bootstrapping a new media‚Äìnative service that serves a long tail need by hovering up the disparate insights contained in pockets digital exhaust across the internet, synthesizing it all with AI, and delivering that value to customers via text/chat, NOT blog posts or video courses.</p>\n<p>It's an exciting time to build...and once Apple launches its long-awaited augmented reality device, things will start to get very, very interesting...</p>\n<p>#ai #digital #entrepreneurship #ar</p>\n",
    "excerpt": "Digital media are fundamentally changing before our eyes (and ears). Right now, thanks to AI (and soon, AR/VR), our relationship with digitized info is...",
