    "content": "<p>Entering a new market is like crossing a foggy river...</p>\n<p>...and OKRs are the steppingstones that help you make it to a better future on the other side.</p>\n<p>Yesterday, I had the opportunity to share a simple approach to objectives and key results with members of the Ask a Chief of Staff community.</p>\n<p>I've been experimenting with it over the past 3 years‚Äîlargely inspired by Christina Wodtke's \"Radical Focus\" and the writings of Hamilton Helmer, Richard Rumelt, and Roger Martin.</p>\n<p>If you're a chief of staff, early stage founder, or innovation unit leader, I hope you might find it useful as a tool that yields insights (and, hopefully, PMF!) fast: <a href=\"https://lnkd.in/dazMzFZT\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://lnkd.in/dazMzFZT</a></p>\n<p>#innovation #okrs #chiefofstaff #strategy\",<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ASXjCW3Ut2o\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ASXjCW3Ut2o</a>,\",MEMBER_NETWORK</p>\n",
