    "content": "<p>Whenever I work with clients on setting quarterly OKRs for the first time, someone inevitably asks to see examples.</p>\n<p>Now, I'm usually a bit hesitant to provide them (at least initially), only because each company is unique‚Äîand the \"correct\" objective and key results that they should be pursuing in the coming quarter is also unique.</p>\n<p>Whenever we see examples, we're always tempted to imitate what we see (can actually pull you off-track) as opposed to emulating it (more likely to be useful).</p>\n<p>But‚Äîgiven that I've written pretty extensive about what makes for good OKRs from first principles, I thought it might be useful to share examples (positive and negative) as well.</p>\n<p>Enjoy and good luck setting those Q1 OKRs!</p>\n<p>(Of course, if you need a little extra help, just shoot me a DM...)</p>\n<p>#okrs #management #strategy #quarterlyresults #startups</p>\n",
