    "id": "post-2022-12-05-7005575099365928960",
    "title": "I've often wondered if Google has been successful not due to their widespread use OKRs, but rather in spite of it.",
    "date": "2022-12-05",
    "content": "<p>I've often wondered if Google has been successful not due to their widespread use OKRs, but rather in spite of it...</p>\n<p>That said, I love OKRs for keeping teams focused‚Äîbut only when there's a sound strategic foundation!</p>\n<p>OKRs\" (the tool + the process) are just a modern instantiation of timeless principles of human coordination toward a common end.</p>\n<p>If you pick the wrong goal (or, IMO, more than one at a time), neither the tool nor the process can fix that.</p>\n<p>Another great Practitioner Insight from Roger Martin:</p>\n",
