    "id": "post-2022-11-08-6995754683784908801",
    "title": "When I work with founders who want to regain their attention from digital distract...",
    "date": "2022-11-08",
    "content": "<p>When I work with founders who want to regain their attention from digital distractions and break free from the chronic stress that accompanies a compulsive e-mail habit, I start by helping them make one simple change‚Ä¶</p>\n<p>It‚Äôs to keep their screen-based devices out of their bedrooms.</p>\n<p>When you‚Äôre ready to start taking attention management seriously, this one change alone will yield more value than almost any other technique.</p>\n<p>But, it is SO HARD.</p>\n<p>For many (if not most) of us, the faint glow of our phone screens is the last thing we see at night and one of the first things we take in in the morning.</p>\n<p>Going cold turkey can be brutally difficult.</p>\n<p>That‚Äôs why I recommend easing the transition by placing two substitutes on your bedside table:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>An engaging book: This doesn‚Äôt have to be a ‚Äúnutritious‚Äù tome. In fact, I recommend selecting something altogether ‚Äújunky‚Äù‚Äîa juicy tabloid, a graphic novel, some pulp fiction. When you‚Äôre craving stimulating information, it‚Äôs easier to resist the urge to check your digital notifications or your favorite social media platform if you have physical media (literally) at hand that satisfies the underlying desire driving your behavior.</li>\n<li>A notebook + expensive pen: If you‚Äôre not in a pure ‚Äúconsumption‚Äù mood, you might instead benefit from focused production. Journaling can be useful and, for some people, articulating their thoughts on paper may scratch this itch; however, I actually recommend using your bedtime notebook primarily as a doodle repository. Let your mind wander freely and see what emerges from the page‚Äîwithout the added pressure of restrictive language. Keep going until you‚Äôre asleep or the page is full with ornate details.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>What‚Äôs interesting about doodling is that it is an exercise in focused concentration, a foundational skill necessary to thrive in the 21st century.</p>\n<p>Compare that to, say, what you get from spending a commensurate amount of time scrolling on TikTok: the opposite‚Äîyou fragment your attention in a mode of pure consumption, which has the effect of disrupting your sleep and degrading your ability to focus and do quality work the next day.</p>\n<p>Want to strengthen your mind and regain your attention from digital distractions?</p>\n<p>Give doodling a try this evening!</p>\n",
