    "title": "A wise man* once told me that a sign of maturity is when your present self consistently thanks your past self.",
    "date": "2022-11-04",
    "content": "<p>A wise man* once told me that a sign of maturity is when your present self consistently thanks your past self.</p>\n<p>When we plan for the future and resist temptation in the present, we are paradoxically better and better off in the present.</p>\n<p>This is why it‚Äôs critical to front load your workday with the most cognitively taxing tasks on your plate.</p>\n<p>Instead of checking your email or catching up on Slack threads, consider creating an asset that will yield compounding value on its own: rohtinize a process to make it easier to delegate, create marketing content, or start testing your strategic assumptions with a rigorous financial model.</p>\n<p>By investing your highest quality attention into the creation of ‚Äúcapital goods‚Äù for knowledge work, you shift your time preference towards the future.</p>\n<p>The east stuff can wait ‚Äòtil the afternoon.</p>\n<p>And, next thing you know, you‚Äôll be thanking your past self every day!</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Asbed Kassis</li>\n</ul>\n",
