    "title": "No matter how much money you raise, there‚Äôs one constraint every founder at every ...",
    "date": "2022-10-24",
    "content": "<p>No matter how much money you raise, there‚Äôs one constraint every founder at every stage will have to deal with‚Ä¶</p>\n<p>It‚Äôs your limited attention.</p>\n<p>The truth is, you only have about 100 waking hours every week.</p>\n<p>And only about four ‚Äúhigh-quality‚Äù hours per day.</p>\n<p>Are you directing your attention toward the right problems?</p>\n<p>Attention is like money. You can spend it frivolously or use it to create wealth.</p>\n<p>Are you ‚Äúpaying‚Äù attention or are you investing it?</p>\n<p>Right now, go look at your iOS or Android screen time analytics and see where those 100 hours went last week‚Ä¶</p>\n<p>Did you create marketing assets? Document processes? Strengthen relationships? Build technology?</p>\n<p>Or did you give your hours to social media, YouTube, email, mobile games, Slack, and frivolous Zoom meetings?</p>\n<p>And what about your teammates? Have you built a culture and a work environment that values focus and outcomes? Is their clear alignment across the company on your long-term mission and vision + shorter-term strategic objective?</p>\n<p>Or do you tolerate distractions that eat away at employee attention (and ultimately your company‚Äôs checking account)?</p>\n<p>As we exit the age of 0% interest rates, investors will expect profitability at earlier stages, and you‚Äôll need to compete with other hungry entrepreneurs for smaller pools of capital.</p>\n<p>The founders who will come out ahead in the next decade are those who master attention management.</p>\n<p>Between now and IPO, every hour counts.</p>\n<p>So, how do you stay focused in the age of digital distractions?</p>\n<p>Share your tips in a comment below üëá</p>\n",
